168	<body>
169	<div class="max">
170	
171	<header>
172	  <h1>🧰 Anycubic Kobra S1 — Complete Maintenance Guide</h1>
173	  <p>Keep your printer running smooth · Step-by-step · Visual checklists</p>
174	</header>
175	
176	<!-- ═══ SCHEDULE ═══ -->
177	<section>
178	  <div class="card">
179	    <h2>📅 Quick-Reference Schedule</h2>
180	    <table class="schedule">
181	      <tr><th>Interval</th><th>Task</th><th>See §</th></tr>
182	      <tr><td><strong>Every print</strong></td><td>Wipe spring steel sheet; check first layer</td><td>9</td></tr>
183	      <tr><td><strong>Weekly</strong></td><td>Inspect fans for dust; check camera lens</td><td>8, 4</td></tr>
184	      <tr><td><strong>Monthly</strong></td><td>Clean &amp; inspect Y-axis linear rods</td><td>2</td></tr>
185	      <tr><td><strong>Every 3 months</strong></td><td>Lubricate Z-axis lead screw</td><td>1</td></tr>
186	      <tr><td><strong>Every 3–5 spools</strong></td><td>Inspect cutter assembly for wear</td><td>5</td></tr>
187	      <tr><td><strong>As needed</strong></td><td>Nozzle cleaning / cold pull; replace silicone sock</td><td>6, 7</td></tr>
188	    </table>
189	    <p class="alert alert-info">🔗 Original source: <a href="https://wiki.anycubic.com/en/fdm-3d-printer/kobra-s1-combo/maintenance-recommendations" target="_blank">Anycubic Wiki — Kobra S1 Maintenance Recommendations</a></p>
190	  </div>
191	</section>
192	
193	<!-- ═══ SAFETY ═══ -->
194	<section>
195	  <div class="card">
196	    <h2>⚠️ Safety First</h2>
197	    <ul>
198	      <li><strong>Always power off and disconnect</strong> the printer before cleaning or touching moving parts (Z-screw lubrication is the one exception — motor must be on to move axes).</li>
199	      <li>Let the hotend cool below 40 °C before handling the nozzle or silicone sock.</li>
200	      <li>Use insulated gloves when cleaning a heated nozzle.</li>
